    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 887.0112/12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 390.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of the
                    Department’s instruction No. 123 of the 13th instant, instructing me as to the
                    reply to be made to President Gómez’s note of the 19th ultimo in regard to the
                    proposed Zapata Swamp Concession.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to report that I yesterday addressed a note to
                    President Gómez in the language desired by the Department.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Gibson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
